data.name: Pork Fried Rice
data.quickTastyDescription: A savory and satisfying dish, packed with tender pork and vibrant vegetables, all stir-fried with perfectly cooked rice for a delicious meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: Heat vegetable oil in a large pan or wok over medium-high heat.
Add diced pork tenderloin and cook until browned and cooked through, about 5-7 minutes.
Add the diced carrot and peas, stir-frying for another 2-3 minutes until tender.
Push the pork and vegetables to one side of the pan, and pour the beaten egg into the empty side. Scramble the egg until fully cooked, then mix it with the pork and vegetables.
Add the cooked rice to the pan, breaking up any clumps with a spatula.
Pour in soy sauce, and sprinkle with garlic powder and ginger powder. Stir well to combine all ingredients and heat through, about 2-3 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper to taste, and mix in the sliced green onions just before serving.
